# Git Guardian Default Workflow

After any subagent completes a task that may have modified files, run the `git-guardian` subagent before ending the turn.

## Required sequence

1. Detect whether files changed in the workspace.
2. If changes exist, invoke `git-guardian` to handle:
   - commit preparation and user confirmation
   - push/pull confirmations
   - repository bootstrap when no GitHub remote exists
3. Do not auto-push without explicit user approval.
4. If no files changed, skip commit flow and report "no changes to commit".

## Commit source policy

When preparing a commit, prioritize concise summaries from `logs/` subagent logs and include bilingual commit text (EN + RU) plus `Log source: <filename>`.
